<item>
            <title>[LU-10265] lustre_rsync DNE support</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10265</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I found there is something wrong when sync with striped directory.&lt;br/&gt;
 Some directories metadata (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;./dirA&lt;/tt&gt; ) in MDT1 but there files (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;dirA/xxxx&lt;/tt&gt; ) are in MDT0.&lt;br/&gt;
 The directory did not created when sync MDT0 changelog first, then &lt;tt&gt;lustre_rsync&lt;/tt&gt; put these files to &lt;tt&gt;.lustrerepl&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Test striped directory lustre_rsync steps.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160; created striped directory and set default striped.&lt;br/&gt;
 &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs setdirstripe -c 2 testdir&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and set default by &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs setdirstripe -c 2 -D testdir&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;copy some files with directories to this directory&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;do &lt;tt&gt;lustre_rsync MDT0000&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;do &lt;tt&gt;lustre_rsync MDT0001&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
